ify without running tests. Using `javap` could be an option since it avoids compiling or executing the tests. But I feel like invoking something simple like `jshell` would be akin to running code, which I want to avoid. Maybe I could alternatively add a test stub for the optional `oracle.dms` classes to ensure that the `LiveDMSFactory` constructor succeeds adequately and remains robust in a native environment.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying type correctness**\\n\\nI'm considering how type correctness is verified and the idea that classes might be loaded lazily. I remember that a NoClassDefFoundError can happen if a superclass or interface is missing, but not necessarily for field or method types until reflection is used to get declared methods. Also, I realize that the invokevirtual instruction doesn't resolve symbolic references until execution, which makes things interesting. Finally, I note that Class.forName generally succeeds, and the constructor object exists when newInstance is called.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering class loading approach**\\n\\nI’m thinking about how to avoid depending on order. Maybe I can create an isolated ClassLoader to load the ojdbc jar after setting a specific property to true? But, wait, dynamic class loading in Native might not be supported, which complicates it. I need to also ensure there are no version hardcodes involved. Hmm, I’ll need to inspect how AssertJ and JUnit are used for testing style and correctness.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_EKzhqshdxt99SkdOejGjtSHD|fc_0ce4c7fba8dbf62b0169f845a59ee881959e4a4a0fd1a64761", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/com.oracle.database.jdbc/ojdbc11/23.8.0.25.04/src/test/java/com_oracle_database_jdbc/ojdbc11/OracleDriverTest.java", "limit": 120}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1024, "output": 1338, "cacheRead": 20480, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 22842, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777878415042, "responseId": "resp_0ce4c7fba8dbf62b0169f8458f9fe8819598687a856c91f5be"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_EKzhqshdxt99SkdOejGjtSHD|fc_0ce4c7fba8dbf62b0169f845a59ee881959e4a4a0fd1a64761", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage com_oracle_database_jdbc.ojdbc11;\n\nimport oracle.jdbc.OracleConnection;\nimport oracle.jdbc.driver.OracleDriver;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Timeout;\n\nimport java.sql.DriverPropertyInfo;\nimport java.sql.SQLException;\nimport java.util.Arrays;\nimport java.util.Map;\nimport java.util.Properties;\nimport java.util.function.Function;\n\nimport static java.util.stream.Collectors.toMap;\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\nimport static org.junit.jupiter.api.Assertions.assertThrows;\n\npublic class OracleDriverTest {\n    private static final String UNREACHABLE_THIN_URL = \"jdbc:oracle:thin:@127.0.0.1:1/FREEPDB1\";\n\n    @Test\n    void createsPropertyInfoFromOracleConnectionConstants() throws SQLException {\n        OracleDriver driver = new OracleDriver();\n\n        DriverPropertyInfo[] propertyInfos = driver.getPropertyInfo(UNREACHABLE_THIN_URL, new Properties());\n\n        Map<String, DriverPropertyInfo> propertyInfoByName = Arrays.stream(propertyInfos)\n                .collect(toMap(propertyInfo -> propertyInfo.name, Function.identity(), (first, second) -> first));\n        assertThat(propertyInfoByName).containsKeys(\n                OracleConnection.CONNECTION_PROPERTY_DEFAULT_ROW_PREFETCH,\n                OracleConnection.CONNECTION_PROPERTY_THIN_NET_CONNECT_TIMEOUT);\n        assertThat(propertyInfoByName.get(OracleConnection.CONNECTION_PROPERTY_DEFAULT_ROW_PREFETCH).value)\n                .isEqualTo(OracleConnection.CONNECTION_PROPERTY_DEFAULT_ROW_PREFETCH_DEFAULT);\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    @Timeout(10)\n    void loadsThinDriverExtensionBeforeOpeningNetworkConnection() {\n        OracleDriver driver = new OracleDriver();\n        Properties properties = new Properties();\n        properties.setProperty(OracleConnection.CONNECTION_PROPERTY_USER_NAME, \"metadata_test_user\");\n        properties.setProperty(OracleConnection.CONNECTION_PROPERTY_PASSWORD, \"metadata_test_password\");\n        properties.setProperty(OracleConnection.CONNECTION_PROPERTY_THIN_NET_CONNECT_TIMEOUT, \"1000\");\n\n        assertThrows(SQLException.class, () -> driver.connect(UNREACHABLE_THIN_URL, properties));\n    }\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777878437986}]}
