nly work within that class. Let’s look into what earlier tests trigger DMSFactory.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Reorganizing test order**\\n\\nI need to ensure DMSFactoryTest runs early, but I’m unsure how the test discovery order is determined by native-image JUnit. It might depend on the classpath scan order. The file name DMSFactoryTest is placed after Sdp, which seems like it might affect sorting. The output now shows OracleRef, Converter, and OracleTypeADT first, not based on class name. Perhaps I could add a static field to relevant tests, or even create a new class named AAAADMSFactoryTest for better organization.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Evaluating Java bytecode**\\n\\nI'm looking into the use of `class` in `javap` for an interface, which seems to refer to `InterfaceMethod` for `NounIntf`. It feels like there’s a contradiction there since an interface ideally shouldn’t be referred to as a class. I'm curious if we can define the interface correctly. I’m also checking how the bytecode utilizes `checkcast` to convert from the reference type `Sensor` to `StateIntf`. There’s a lot going on with the bytecode here!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_2vaahC17uL2DiBJ8RuucZBO2|fc_0ce4c7fba8dbf62b0169f846c9d3008195b0513960c3749e7d", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "mkdir -p tests/src/com.oracle.database.jdbc/ojdbc11/23.8.0.25.04/src/test/java/oracle/dms/console tests/src/com.oracle.database.jdbc/ojdbc11/23.8.0.25.04/src/test/java/oracle/dms/instrument tests/src/com.oracle.database.jdbc/ojdbc11/23.8.0.25.04/src/test/java/oracle/dms/context tests/src/com.oracle.database.jdbc/ojdbc11/23.8.0.25.04/src/test/java/oracle/core/ojdl"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1235, "output": 1689, "cacheRead": 28672, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 31596, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777878705339,